2
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:36,078
Are we still partners?

3
00:00:38,121 --> 00:00:40,624
<i>We've been business partners
for 155 weeks now</i>

4
00:00:40,749 --> 00:00:43,293
<i>We're sitting next to each other
for the first time today,</i>

5
00:00:43,418 --> 00:00:45,754
<i>We seldom see each other.</i>

6
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:49,132
<i>I know too well that man
can hardly control his passion.</i>

7
00:00:49,299 --> 00:00:51,802
<i>Partners should never get
emotionally involved with each other.</i>

8
00:00:52,052 --> 00:00:54,638
FALLEN ANGELS

9
00:04:29,978 --> 00:04:34,232
<i>A message for 3662.</i>

10
00:04:34,357 --> 00:04:36,443
<i>I'm meeting his friends tomorrow</i>

11
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,696
<i>Ask him to let me know where.</i>

12
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:58,799
<i>Most people work from 9..00 to 5..00.</i>

13
00:04:59,466 --> 00:05:01,551
<i>I'm just the opposite.</i>

14
00:05:02,219 --> 00:05:04,679
<i>My job is simple.</i>

15
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:08,141
<i>I visit some "friends"
once in a while.</i>

16
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:11,019
<i>I don't know any of them.</i>

17
00:05:11,603 --> 00:05:13,897
<i>And I'm not interested
in them either.</i>

18
00:05:14,231 --> 00:05:16,650
<i>Because they'll soon be gone forever.</i>

19
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:02,297
Going out?

20
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:03,673
Yes.

21
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:11,806
<i>One's profession is very often
determined by one's personality,</i>

22
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:15,352
<i>The best thing about my profession</i>

23
00:07:15,518 --> 00:07:17,312
<i>is there's no need
to make any decisions.</i>

24
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:20,231
<i>Who's to die, when, where-</i>

25
00:07:20,357 --> 00:07:22,150
<i>it's all been planned by others.</i>

26
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:23,902
<i>I'm a lazy person.</i>

27
00:07:24,027 --> 00:07:27,197
<i>I like people to arrange things for me.</i>

28
00:07:27,364 --> 00:07:29,824
<i>That's why I need a partner.</i>

29
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:08,149
Ming?

30
00:10:10,401 --> 00:10:11,528
Ming!

31
00:10:12,862 --> 00:10:14,864
You're Ming, aren't you?

32
00:10:15,031 --> 00:10:17,408
Remember me?
My name's Hoi.

33
00:10:17,534 --> 00:10:21,371
Don't you remember me?
I was always number one in grade school.

34
00:10:21,496 --> 00:10:22,831
- Remember?
- Yeah.

35
00:10:22,956 --> 00:10:24,165
What a coincidence!

36
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:27,836
If my Mercedes hadn't broken down,
I wouldn't have run into you here.

37
00:10:27,961 --> 00:10:31,047
<i>Every person has his own past.</i>

38
00:10:31,214 --> 00:10:32,757
<i>Even if you're a killer,</i>

39
00:10:32,882 --> 00:10:35,218
<i>you still have classmates
from grade school around</i>

40
00:10:35,385 --> 00:10:36,970
<i>Every time I run into them,</i>

41
00:10:37,095 --> 00:10:39,764
<i>they ask me the same questions.</i>

42
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:43,309
What kind of work do you do?

43
00:10:43,893 --> 00:10:46,729
Give me your card
so we can keep in touch.

44
00:10:46,855 --> 00:10:48,773
Maybe we could work together.

45
00:10:48,898 --> 00:10:51,609
That would be great.
Always lookin' to make a buck.

46
00:10:54,904 --> 00:10:57,991
Your own business?
That's worth breaking your back for!

47
00:10:58,116 --> 00:10:59,909
You married?

48
00:11:00,076 --> 00:11:02,745
Don't tell me you can't find a girl!

49
00:11:03,538 --> 00:11:05,748
What? A son!

50
00:11:06,207 --> 00:11:07,876
Looks exactly like you!

51
00:11:08,251 --> 00:11:11,421
What's this-your wife's black?

52
00:11:12,088 --> 00:11:15,341
I mean... smart move!
Black grows on you.

53
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:17,594
Your skin color's different,

54
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:19,804
but you make a nice couple.

55
00:11:20,263 --> 00:11:22,265
Hey, are you insured?

56
00:11:22,432 --> 00:11:24,100
Maybe you can help me out.

57
00:11:24,225 --> 00:11:26,227
I've been in the business
over ten years.

58
00:11:26,352 --> 00:11:27,604
You might not know,

59
00:11:27,770 --> 00:11:32,567
but I'm rated the top insurance broker
in all Southeast Asia.

60
00:11:32,692 --> 00:11:36,571
I'm being interviewed
by the newspaper in a <i>few</i> days.

61
00:11:36,696 --> 00:11:38,865
For old time's sake,

62
00:11:39,115 --> 00:11:44,412
I'll work out the best plan for you.
You never can tell.

63
00:11:44,537 --> 00:11:47,081
God forbid, but what if
something should happen?

64
00:11:47,207 --> 00:11:48,958
It's not just for you.

65
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:51,628
I see you travel a lot for work.

66
00:11:51,794 --> 00:11:54,714
If not for yourself,
think about your wife and little boy.

67
00:11:54,839 --> 00:11:59,510
<i>I often wonder if any insurance company
would insure a professional killer.</i>

68
00:11:59,636 --> 00:12:01,596
<i>I'd really like to help him out,</i>

69
00:12:01,721 --> 00:12:03,932
<i>but I wouldn't know
whom to name as beneficiary.</i>

70
00:12:04,057 --> 00:12:07,644
Remember that girl with the big boobs?
The one we were both after years ago?

71
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:10,980
We're getting married next week.
Here's an invitation.

72
00:12:13,149 --> 00:12:15,068
Sorry-just write your own name on it.

73
00:12:15,485 --> 00:12:18,488
Come a little early.
I'll write up the policy for you.

74
00:12:18,613 --> 00:12:20,406
And bring your wife.
Bye-bye.

75
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:26,329
<i>A few years back, I paid a black woman
$30 to have her picture taken with me,</i>

76
00:12:26,496 --> 00:12:29,666
<i>so that if people asked,
I could say she was my wife.</i>

77
00:12:30,041 --> 00:12:33,211
<i>And the kid in the picture-
I just bought him an ice-cream cone.</i>

78
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:37,340
<i>I've always wanted to go
to a wedding,</i>

79
00:12:38,675 --> 00:12:42,011
<i>but I know very well
it's not my kind of scene.</i>

80
00:14:38,461 --> 00:14:40,546
<i>Going through a person's trash</i>

81
00:14:40,671 --> 00:14:43,758
<i>can tell you a lot about them.</i>

82
00:14:45,468 --> 00:14:48,221
<i>He comes to this bar a lot.</i>

83
00:14:49,347 --> 00:14:51,015
<i>Maybe 'cause it's quiet.</i>

84
00:14:53,559 --> 00:14:56,813
<i>Sometimes I sit in his usual seat.</i>

85
00:14:58,106 --> 00:15:00,900
<i>Lets me feel close to him.</i>

86
00:15:07,782 --> 00:15:10,993
<i>Some people you really don't want
to get too close to.</i>

87
00:15:13,454 --> 00:15:16,374
<i>Find out too much about a person
and you lose interest.</i>

88
00:15:20,128 --> 00:15:22,713
<i>I'm the practical kind</i>

89
00:15:23,798 --> 00:15:26,050
<i>I know how to make myself happy,</i>

90
00:20:01,992 --> 00:20:04,620
No, he hasn't come back yet.

91
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:06,080
You telling the truth?

92
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:08,666
Why should I lie?

93
00:20:10,084 --> 00:20:14,088
- You live here?
- Something wrong with that?

94
00:20:14,213 --> 00:20:15,881
Have you seen this person around?

95
00:20:16,006 --> 00:20:17,466
No.

96
00:20:29,979 --> 00:20:31,439
Don't come out yet.

97
00:20:31,564 --> 00:20:33,566
The cops are still here.

98
00:20:47,121 --> 00:20:48,998
You know where he is. Tell us.

99
00:20:49,123 --> 00:20:52,042
<i>You rub elbows
with a lot of people everyday,</i>

100
00:20:52,168 --> 00:20:56,005
<i>Some strangers might become
your friends or even confidants.</i>

101
00:20:57,047 --> 00:21:01,135
<i>But I know very well these cops
will never be my confidants.</i>

102
00:21:02,011 --> 00:21:03,721
<i>My name is Ho Chi Moo.</i>

103
00:21:03,846 --> 00:21:05,806
<i>I was prisoner number 223.</i>

104
00:21:05,931 --> 00:21:09,810
I haven't seen him in days.
I'll let you know when he comes back.

105
00:21:10,811 --> 00:21:13,689
I saw him come in.
You'd better tell the truth.

106
00:21:17,485 --> 00:21:19,737
Stop making faces!
Stand still!

107
00:21:39,507 --> 00:21:41,217
<i>I'm a happy man.</i>

108
00:21:41,383 --> 00:21:43,385
<i>I was very talkative when I was small.</i>

109
00:21:43,844 --> 00:21:47,556
<i>But at age five, I ate
a can of pineapple that had expired,</i>

110
00:21:48,516 --> 00:21:50,893
<i>and I stopped talking.</i>

111
00:21:51,769 --> 00:21:54,438
<i>For that reason,
I have very few friends.</i>

112
00:21:54,563 --> 00:21:57,858
<i>I found it very hard
to find work too.</i>

113
00:21:57,983 --> 00:22:00,778
<i>I finally decided to be my own boss.</i>

114
00:22:19,129 --> 00:22:21,882
<i>Having no capital,
the only thing I can do</i>

115
00:22:22,007 --> 00:22:24,134
<i>is sneak into
other people's shops after hours</i>

116
00:22:24,260 --> 00:22:26,554
<i>and run my own business.</i>

117
00:22:26,929 --> 00:22:28,889
<i>I'm not a freeloader.</i>

118
00:22:29,014 --> 00:22:32,810
<i>I just think it makes sense,
since the rent's already been paid,</i>

119
00:22:32,935 --> 00:22:34,812
<i>to run the business around the clock.</i>

120
00:22:34,937 --> 00:22:37,565
<i>Who says nobody
buys pork at 3.-00 a.m.?</i>

121
00:22:37,690 --> 00:22:39,775
<i>I came yesterday
to buy some, didn't I?</i>

122
00:22:40,276 --> 00:22:41,819
<i>If you want to do business,</i>

123
00:22:41,944 --> 00:22:44,113
<i>you have to take
each customer's needs into account.</i>

124
00:22:45,239 --> 00:22:49,159
<i>Buddha said,
"If I don't descend into hell, who will?"</i>

125
00:22:49,285 --> 00:22:51,120
<i>When you're the boss,
you have to be kind,</i>

126
00:22:51,245 --> 00:22:52,705
<i>caring and tolerant.</i>

127
00:22:52,830 --> 00:22:54,957
<i>You can't just look to your own gain.</i>

128
00:22:55,124 --> 00:22:58,377
<i>I know very well
there's no such thing as a free lunch,</i>

129
00:22:58,502 --> 00:23:02,172
<i>so I always work very hard
until the wee hours.</i>

130
00:23:02,506 --> 00:23:05,843
<i>I don't make a lot of money,
but I'm happy,</i>

131
00:23:23,485 --> 00:23:25,863
Are you nuts? Why should I let you
wash my clothes?

132
00:23:25,988 --> 00:23:27,948
I'm a beggar.
I don't need laundry done!

133
00:23:28,073 --> 00:23:30,326
I don't need it!

134
00:23:30,492 --> 00:23:32,661
Leave me alone!

135
00:23:32,828 --> 00:23:35,748
Are you nuts?
Keep your hands off my clothes!

136
00:23:35,873 --> 00:23:38,208
Give me back my clothes!

137
00:23:38,334 --> 00:23:40,753
Hands off!
I'll beat you up!

138
00:23:40,878 --> 00:23:42,504
Okay, I'll pay!

139
00:23:42,755 --> 00:23:46,550
I'll pay you,
if it's money you want.

140
00:23:46,675 --> 00:23:48,177
You're a lunatic!

141
00:23:50,846 --> 00:23:53,349
Don't push me!
I don't want any eggplant!

142
00:23:53,515 --> 00:23:55,434
You can't make me buy it!

143
00:23:55,559 --> 00:23:59,229
I'm single.
What would people think?

144
00:23:59,355 --> 00:24:00,689
Not even if they're free!

145
00:24:00,814 --> 00:24:02,691
I'll take some melon.

146
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:06,654
Here!

147
00:24:12,534 --> 00:24:15,371
This is huge!
Are you out of your mind?

148
00:24:18,207 --> 00:24:19,583
Stop that!

149
00:24:19,917 --> 00:24:24,046
I washed my hair yesterday.

150
00:24:30,678 --> 00:24:32,262
Ouch! Easy!

151
00:24:32,513 --> 00:24:36,392
My head doesn't itch-
stop scratching it!

152
00:24:38,394 --> 00:24:40,688
I just came down for a late snack.

153
00:24:40,813 --> 00:24:42,940
I don't need a shampoo.

154
00:24:46,068 --> 00:24:49,405
I give up.
Do whatever you want.

155
00:24:54,702 --> 00:24:56,245
No!

156
00:24:58,414 --> 00:25:00,833
I don't want a shave!

157
00:25:08,173 --> 00:25:09,633
Hands off!

158
00:25:13,262 --> 00:25:18,017
Listen, I'm no regular guy.
I have underworld connections.

159
00:25:21,311 --> 00:25:24,857
I really don't want a shave.
How about-

160
00:25:24,982 --> 00:25:27,443
I'll pay you, okay?

161
00:25:30,988 --> 00:25:33,198
A double cone, please.

162
00:25:35,451 --> 00:25:36,952
Oh, no, it's you!

163
00:25:37,077 --> 00:25:38,871
Sorry.

164
00:25:50,007 --> 00:25:52,676
Stop pulling my hair.

165
00:25:52,801 --> 00:25:55,304
I'll climb in myself.

166
00:25:56,889 --> 00:25:59,308
Sorry!

167
00:26:02,352 --> 00:26:04,146
I'm coming in.

168
00:26:10,486 --> 00:26:14,114
Hello? It's me.
What are you doing?

169
00:26:17,034 --> 00:26:19,328
Go to bed. Don't wait for me.

170
00:26:21,497 --> 00:26:23,332
I'm having some ice cream.

171
00:26:24,708 --> 00:26:28,128
Uh, no, it's more than a scoop or two.

172
00:26:29,254 --> 00:26:32,007
I don't know how much more
I'll have to eat.

173
00:26:33,383 --> 00:26:37,054
No, it's not an eating contest.
Of course I'll have to pay!

174
00:26:41,058 --> 00:26:44,269
Yeah, but this guy won't let me...

175
00:26:44,937 --> 00:26:47,856
I don't know how to explain,
but it's the truth.

176
00:26:49,358 --> 00:26:51,944
Come see for yourself
if you don't believe me.

177
00:26:52,069 --> 00:26:53,612
Hello?

178
00:26:58,158 --> 00:27:01,286
No, I can't eat that!

179
00:27:04,706 --> 00:27:07,292
What if my mustache catches on fire?

180
00:27:08,377 --> 00:27:10,629
This isn't funny anymore.

181
00:27:14,216 --> 00:27:16,385
Why are you doing this?

182
00:27:17,719 --> 00:27:19,221
I said to come by yourself.

183
00:27:19,388 --> 00:27:21,557
I didn't tell you
to bring the whole family.

184
00:27:22,391 --> 00:27:24,977
Dad's too old for all this ice cream.

185
00:27:25,435 --> 00:27:27,396
What if something happens?

186
00:27:28,772 --> 00:27:31,441
The kids have to go to school tomorrow.

187
00:27:32,109 --> 00:27:34,069
Think about that.

188
00:27:39,074 --> 00:27:44,246
Has anyone in Hong Kong ever died
from too much ice cream?

189
00:27:44,872 --> 00:27:47,457
I don't want to be the first.

190
00:27:48,584 --> 00:27:50,794
I'll pay you, okay?

191
00:27:50,919 --> 00:27:55,549
Name a price.
I'll buy it all. Please.

192
00:27:58,594 --> 00:28:01,597
<i>My ice cream may be
a bit more expensive,</i>

193
00:28:01,722 --> 00:28:04,516
<i>but I think this family
is having a great time.</i>

194
00:28:06,393 --> 00:28:08,270
<i>I love ice cream.</i>

195
00:28:08,395 --> 00:28:12,357
<i>When I was little, an ice cream truck
would stop by my house every day,</i>

196
00:28:12,482 --> 00:28:15,611
<i>I was always happy to see it.</i>

197
00:28:16,695 --> 00:28:20,282
<i>Once I asked my dad
why he didn't drive an ice cream truck.</i>

198
00:28:21,074 --> 00:28:22,993
<i>He didn't answer.</i>

199
00:28:23,118 --> 00:28:24,661
<i>I later found out</i>

200
00:28:24,786 --> 00:28:27,456
<i>my mother had been run over
by an ice cream truck.</i>

201
00:28:29,875 --> 00:28:31,668
<i>I was born in Taiwan.</i>

202
00:28:31,793 --> 00:28:34,546
<i>I came to Hong Kong
with my dad when I was five.</i>

203
00:28:35,088 --> 00:28:37,716
<i>He worked as an assistant
at the Chungking Mansions Hotel.</i>

204
00:28:38,300 --> 00:28:42,304
<i>He's rarely talked
since my mother died</i>

205
00:28:42,429 --> 00:28:44,348
<i>No more ice cream, of course.</i>

206
00:28:46,558 --> 00:28:48,894
<i>Maybe the fact
we're both so quiet</i>

207
00:28:49,019 --> 00:28:51,563
<i>explains why we've always been close.</i>

208
00:28:54,358 --> 00:28:56,985
Why are you being so nice to me?

209
00:28:57,110 --> 00:28:58,987
You even bought me ice cream.

210
00:28:59,821 --> 00:29:02,366
You should know
I don't like ice cream.

211
00:29:18,382 --> 00:29:21,927
It's too cold!

212
00:29:22,177 --> 00:29:24,680
It's bad for my health.
Gives me the runs.

213
00:29:38,277 --> 00:29:39,528
Are you nuts?

214
00:29:54,543 --> 00:29:57,504
Hey, open up!
What game are you playing now?

215
00:29:58,213 --> 00:29:59,715
Open this door!

216
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:02,759
What are you doing?

217
00:30:03,218 --> 00:30:05,178
I'll kill you!

218
00:30:05,762 --> 00:30:08,056
Open this door!
Stop playing around!

219
00:30:22,738 --> 00:30:24,740
<i>9090.</i>

220
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:27,576
<i>I'd like to leave a message.</i>

221
00:30:27,743 --> 00:30:30,078
<i>I'm meeting his friends tomorrow</i>

222
00:30:31,079 --> 00:30:32,664
<i>He should let me know where.</i>

223
00:32:16,226 --> 00:32:19,646
I get it. It's clear.

224
00:32:20,689 --> 00:32:25,026
I just wanna make sure
the address was correct.

225
00:32:25,193 --> 00:32:28,113
It was a fast-food store,
not a barber shop.

226
00:32:28,530 --> 00:32:31,867
<i>You may think
we must be making a lot of money,</i>

227
00:32:31,992 --> 00:32:34,494
<i>But how much is a human life worth?</i>

228
00:32:34,619 --> 00:32:36,329
<i>Demand comes and goes.</i>

229
00:32:36,455 --> 00:32:39,040
<i>It's not unusual to have
no business for months.</i>

230
00:32:39,207 --> 00:32:41,001
<i>So, once in a while</i>

231
00:32:41,126 --> 00:32:43,670
<i>I moonlight in the financial field</i>

232
00:32:43,795 --> 00:32:46,047
<i>Like debt collection.</i>

233
00:32:46,214 --> 00:32:47,257
Thanks.

234
00:32:51,887 --> 00:32:53,805
Hold on.
I'll get you the money.

235
00:32:58,393 --> 00:32:59,144
Here.

236
00:34:35,323 --> 00:34:38,326
<i>I don't know why,
but I've been injured a lot lately</i>

237
00:34:38,827 --> 00:34:42,372
<i>I hate digging bullets
out of my own body</i>

238
00:34:43,331 --> 00:34:45,041
<i>It's exhausting.</i>

239
00:34:50,922 --> 00:34:53,049
<i>I turned in early that night,</i>

240
