So why didn't he?

492
00:59:55,342 --> 00:59:57,844
<i>I realized that she still missed Johnny,</i>

493
00:59:58,011 --> 01:00:00,013
<i>It made me feel bad</i>

494
01:00:00,138 --> 01:00:02,474
<i>But I'm an optimist.</i>

495
01:00:02,599 --> 01:00:06,478
<i>I've heard people say
everything has its expiration date.</i>

496
01:00:06,603 --> 01:00:09,815
<i>I wasn't sure this would apply
to her and Johnny,</i>

497
01:00:10,148 --> 01:00:12,818
<i>but I thought it might soon.</i>

498
01:00:26,957 --> 01:00:29,543
<i>I guess I might have been
a little too optimistic.</i>

499
01:00:30,043 --> 01:00:33,004
<i>A few days later,
I asked her to go to a second match.</i>

500
01:00:34,214 --> 01:00:36,091
<i>She didn't show up.</i>

501
01:00:37,300 --> 01:00:40,887
<i>I thought what she had
with Johnny would expire soon.</i>

502
01:00:41,638 --> 01:00:42,889
<i>But as it turned out,</i>

503
01:00:43,056 --> 01:00:45,517
<i>my expiration date came up first.</i>

504
01:00:49,354 --> 01:00:51,982
<i>I got there early
and stayed till everyone was gone.</i>

505
01:00:52,107 --> 01:00:54,317
<i>As the lights of the stadium went dark,</i>

506
01:00:54,442 --> 01:00:56,194
<i>I realized she wasn't gonna show</i>

507
01:00:56,319 --> 01:00:58,989
<i>I was heartbroken.
This couldn't be.</i>

508
01:01:06,913 --> 01:01:09,666
<i>People say breaking up hurts.</i>

509
01:01:10,083 --> 01:01:12,043
<i>That wasn't true for me.</i>

510
01:01:14,045 --> 01:01:15,714
<i>But something strange did happen.</i>

511
01:01:15,839 --> 01:01:19,426
<i>After that day, my blond hair
suddenly disappeared</i>

512
01:01:19,593 --> 01:01:21,761
<i>Just like my first love.</i>

513
01:01:22,762 --> 01:01:26,683
<i>I also began to realize my past behavior
had been very irresponsible.</i>

514
01:01:27,475 --> 01:01:29,686
<i>I shouldn't have taken over
other people's shops,</i>

515
01:01:29,811 --> 01:01:32,272
<i>coming and going as I pleased</i>

516
01:01:33,231 --> 01:01:36,026
<i>Every shop has its own feelings.</i>

517
01:01:36,776 --> 01:01:39,362
<i>This realization
had a profound effect on me.</i>

518
01:01:40,697 --> 01:01:42,449
<i>It prompted me to change my ways.</i>

519
01:01:57,714 --> 01:01:59,174
Welcome.

520
01:02:00,300 --> 01:02:01,509
One person.

521
01:02:02,636 --> 01:02:07,140
Look for our <i>new</i> menu next time.

522
01:02:07,265 --> 01:02:09,017
Am I making you stay overtime?

523
01:02:11,019 --> 01:02:13,104
Get a glass for yourself.
Be my guest.

524
01:02:23,323 --> 01:02:24,449
How's business?

525
01:02:38,296 --> 01:02:40,715
What's it cost
to open a place like this?

526
01:02:57,691 --> 01:02:59,359
Good evening.

527
01:03:01,403 --> 01:03:03,363
You have money?

528
01:03:04,364 --> 01:03:07,784
I was just wondering
what it costs to open a place like this.

529
01:03:08,159 --> 01:03:09,953
Do you have a million?

530
01:03:10,078 --> 01:03:12,956
<i>I had never thought
about going into business before.</i>

531
01:03:13,373 --> 01:03:16,543
<i>When you live in a suitcase,
you don't need a place of your own.</i>

532
01:03:17,377 --> 01:03:19,379
<i>But things had changed</i>

533
01:03:19,504 --> 01:03:21,423
<i>I had to start planning
for the future.</i>

534
01:03:22,882 --> 01:03:25,844
<i>That night,
I had a nice chat with the manager.</i>

535
01:03:26,511 --> 01:03:29,389
<i>He even offered a helping hand</i>

536
01:03:30,432 --> 01:03:32,600
<i>should I ever open my own shop.</i>

537
01:03:33,727 --> 01:03:36,021
- Another beer?
- Sure, one more.

538
01:03:54,372 --> 01:03:56,750
How much money do you have?

539
01:04:12,015 --> 01:04:14,601
<i>I stayed away from that bar
for some time,</i>

540
01:04:16,144 --> 01:04:18,813
<i>partly because I didn't want
to hear song number 1818.</i>

541
01:04:20,106 --> 01:04:23,109
<i>But there are some things
you can't escape.</i>

542
01:04:24,694 --> 01:04:27,822
<i>I've never returned
to that restaurant since that night.</i>

543
01:05:00,397 --> 01:05:04,943
<i>Wishing you good fortune
and long life to reach the heavens</i>

544
01:05:05,193 --> 01:05:09,197
<i>Wishing you a happy birthday</i>

545
01:05:09,739 --> 01:05:13,993
<i>May this day be joyous
for you every year</i>

546
01:05:14,160 --> 01:05:18,498
<i>Best wishes to you</i>

547
01:05:56,703 --> 01:06:00,123
<i>How are you, my boy?</i>

548
01:06:02,917 --> 01:06:05,378
<i>Your dad's fine.
Don't worry about me.</i>

549
01:06:09,549 --> 01:06:11,384
<i>Soon it'll be your birthday,</i>

550
01:06:12,552 --> 01:06:14,929
<i>I'm sorry I can't come home.</i>

551
01:06:16,264 --> 01:06:19,184
<i>Is your mother feeling better?</i>

552
01:06:20,935 --> 01:06:24,898
<i>Is your sister behaving herself?</i>

553
01:06:31,362 --> 01:06:33,907
<i>Sato-san is a real family man.</i>

554
01:06:35,158 --> 01:06:39,245
<i>He was a film director
before he opened this place.</i>

555
01:06:40,163 --> 01:06:45,627
<i>So he always communicates
with his family by making a videotape.</i>

556
01:06:47,837 --> 01:06:51,424
<i>I'm sure his son must be very happy
to receive his videotapes.</i>

557
01:06:53,051 --> 01:06:55,428
<i>Sometimes I want
to try the same thing.</i>

558
01:06:55,595 --> 01:06:58,932
<i>But I don't know
who I'd send my tapes to.</i>

559
01:06:59,849 --> 01:07:02,644
<i>I don't want to end up
sending them to myself</i>

560
01:07:13,696 --> 01:07:21,120
<i>You whom I hold in my heart</i>

561
01:07:23,581 --> 01:07:31,256
<i>Why did you leave my side</i>

562
01:07:34,092 --> 01:07:37,804
<i>Because of you</i>

563
01:07:38,638 --> 01:07:42,850
<i>I'm sad all the time</i>

564
01:07:43,643 --> 01:07:48,565
<i>I miss you with all my heart</i>

565
01:07:53,653 --> 01:07:57,198
<i>My beloved</i>

566
01:07:58,700 --> 01:08:02,078
<i>Come back to me</i>

567
01:08:03,746 --> 01:08:09,168
<i>Hurry back to my side</i>

568
01:08:10,461 --> 01:08:12,839
<i>Though I'm not like Sato-san,</i>

569
01:08:12,964 --> 01:08:16,050
<i>I can feel the same happiness as his son
on receiving his father's tape.</i>

570
01:09:10,855 --> 01:09:13,399
Get out of here!

571
01:09:32,293 --> 01:09:35,838
I've got nothing to say.
I want to go to sleep.

572
01:09:43,012 --> 01:09:46,766
Are you crazy?

573
01:09:47,016 --> 01:09:49,560
Get out of here!

574
01:10:00,780 --> 01:10:01,948
Go away!

575
01:10:50,413 --> 01:10:55,710
<i>Later that night, I discovered Dad
secretly watching the tape.</i>

576
01:10:56,669 --> 01:10:58,504
<i>He really enjoyed it.</i>

577
01:10:59,338 --> 01:11:01,799
<i>I'm usually very bad at details,</i>

578
01:11:02,383 --> 01:11:06,679
<i>but I remember very well
that it was his 60th birthday,</i>

579
01:11:07,847 --> 01:11:11,934
<i>He kept laughing as he watched it.
Who knows what he found so funny,</i>

580
01:11:12,059 --> 01:11:14,270
<i>But I know he was happy,</i>

581
01:11:16,147 --> 01:11:18,191
Stupid kid!

582
01:11:42,632 --> 01:11:44,634
<i>When you've worked
with someone for a long time,</i>

583
01:11:44,759 --> 01:11:47,887
<i>he can have a certain effect on you.</i>

584
01:11:49,180 --> 01:11:51,098
<i>I knew that fragrance very well.</i>

585
01:11:51,891 --> 01:11:55,311
<i>I just wasn't used
to smelling it on another woman.</i>

586
01:12:01,526 --> 01:12:04,111
This suit fits me well.

587
01:12:04,529 --> 01:12:06,656
But I think it's shrunk a little.

588
01:12:11,994 --> 01:12:14,997
I never liked this fragrance
all that much.

589
01:12:17,208 --> 01:12:19,919
This afternoon
I smelled it on another woman.

590
01:12:21,879 --> 01:12:23,881
She wants to see you very much.

591
01:12:24,173 --> 01:12:26,425
I set up a meeting for you with her.

592
01:12:28,094 --> 01:12:29,762
You're not gonna go, right?

593
01:12:34,225 --> 01:12:37,436
You should go.
That way you could clear things up.

594
01:12:40,731 --> 01:12:43,943
Then again,
it's even better if you don't go.

595
01:12:49,866 --> 01:12:51,701
I know you'll go.

596
01:12:53,244 --> 01:12:54,954
You can have this back.

597
01:13:48,007 --> 01:13:50,092
I want...

598
01:13:51,302 --> 01:13:52,762
a bag of chips.

599
01:13:53,679 --> 01:13:55,848
The yellow ones, not the red.

600
01:14:33,386 --> 01:14:36,597
<i>They sat there together
for a long time that day,</i>

601
01:14:36,931 --> 01:14:39,058
<i>I wonder what they said
to each other.</i>

602
01:14:39,892 --> 01:14:42,103
<i>It rained the whole time.</i>

603
01:14:42,228 --> 01:14:43,729
<i>I started to think,</i>

604
01:14:43,896 --> 01:14:46,732
<i>"It's raining so hard
How will I get home by myself?"</i>

605
01:15:03,249 --> 01:15:05,292
<i>Just when I really needed a raincoat,</i>

606
01:15:06,419 --> 01:15:08,254
<i>he returned to my side.</i>

607
01:15:12,091 --> 01:15:14,135
<i>It would be so great</i>

608
01:15:15,052 --> 01:15:16,679
<i>if it could rain forever.</i>

609
01:15:21,434 --> 01:15:22,977
I'm not coming up.

610
01:15:27,690 --> 01:15:29,608
Then why'd you walk me home?

611
01:15:31,402 --> 01:15:34,113
You should have let me
come back alone!

612
01:15:34,280 --> 01:15:36,365
I was thinking of coming back
by myself anyway.

613
01:15:36,490 --> 01:15:39,660
Why did you do that?
Think it'd be easier on me this way?

614
01:15:40,327 --> 01:15:41,746
You're crazy!

615
01:15:41,871 --> 01:15:45,124
Fuck off!
I never want to see you again!

616
01:15:47,835 --> 01:15:49,670
I thought we had agreed on this.

617
01:15:49,795 --> 01:15:52,548
Not me!
I never agreed to anything!

618
01:15:52,673 --> 01:15:56,802
I asked you not to see her, but you did.
Now what do you want from me?

619
01:15:57,970 --> 01:16:00,306
You think I'm a fool?

620
01:16:00,431 --> 01:16:02,475
Get lost!

621
01:16:04,018 --> 01:16:06,771
Liar!

622
01:16:12,485 --> 01:16:13,444
Give me your arm.

623
01:16:19,325 --> 01:16:20,993
Why'd you do that?

624
01:16:24,163 --> 01:16:26,165
Can't I leave you a memento?

625
01:16:26,832 --> 01:16:30,377
You might forget my face,
but not my bite.

626
01:16:34,048 --> 01:16:38,177
But my face is easy to remember.
I have a mole.

627
01:16:38,344 --> 01:16:43,516
If a woman with a mole on her face
comes up to you on the street,

628
01:16:46,060 --> 01:16:48,521
it could be me.

629
01:16:52,399 --> 01:16:54,527
You won't remember me.

630
01:16:58,489 --> 01:16:59,824
Yes, I will.

631
01:17:29,103 --> 01:17:30,855
<i>Do I remember her?</i>

632
01:17:31,105 --> 01:17:33,315
<i>Actually it's not that important.</i>

633
01:17:33,440 --> 01:17:34,859
<i>For her,</i>

634
01:17:35,317 --> 01:17:37,862
<i>I'm just a stopover
on the journey of her life.</i>

635
01:17:37,987 --> 01:17:40,447
<i>I hope she reaches
her destination soon</i>

636
01:17:40,573 --> 01:17:43,200
<i>and finds a man who really loves her.</i>

637
01:17:43,993 --> 01:17:46,537
<i>We all need a partner.</i>

638
01:17:47,872 --> 01:17:50,749
<i>When will I find mine?</i>

639
01:17:57,965 --> 01:18:00,134
Are we still partners?

640
01:18:22,031 --> 01:18:24,700
<i>I didn't know
how to answer that question.</i>

641
01:18:25,159 --> 01:18:28,287
<i>I had come to look at partners
from a new angle.</i>

642
01:18:29,121 --> 01:18:31,957
<i>As a business partner,
she was perfect.</i>

643
01:18:32,791 --> 01:18:36,045
<i>But she wasn't the kind of partner
you could spend your life with.</i>

644
01:18:37,963 --> 01:18:40,257
I'd like to terminate
our business relationship.

645
01:18:54,063 --> 01:18:55,814
Do me one last favor, will you?

646
01:19:05,824 --> 01:19:07,826
<i>I don't know why I agreed</i>

647
01:19:10,829 --> 01:19:12,748
<i>Maybe because
it was the last time.</i>

648
01:19:35,521 --> 01:19:38,107
I want to place
an advertisement for my friend.

649
01:19:41,860 --> 01:19:43,362
On the front page.

650
01:23:11,862 --> 01:23:13,530
<i>The best thing about my profession</i>

651
01:23:13,655 --> 01:23:16,116
<i>is there's no need
to make any decisions.</i>

652
01:23:16,241 --> 01:23:18,243
<i>Who's to die, when, where-</i>

653
01:23:18,410 --> 01:23:20,412
<i>it's all been planned by others.</i>

654
01:23:21,663 --> 01:23:23,457
<i>I'm a lazy person.</i>

655
01:23:24,249 --> 01:23:26,877
<i>I like people to arrange things for me.</i>

656
01:23:27,252 --> 01:23:29,213
<i>It's been a bit different lately</i>

657
01:23:29,755 --> 01:23:31,924
<i>I want to change this habit.</i>

658
01:23:32,758 --> 01:23:35,010
<i>I don't know
if it's a good decision or not,</i>

659
01:23:35,594 --> 01:23:38,472
<i>but at least it's mine.</i>

660
01:24:29,064 --> 01:24:31,733
<i>Old people say taking someone's picture
shortens that person's life.</i>

661
01:24:31,984 --> 01:24:34,069
<i>I'm not sure it's true.</i>

662
01:24:35,529 --> 01:24:37,948
<i>One evening, Dad wasn't feeling well.</i>

663
01:24:38,407 --> 01:24:40,158
<i>I took him to the hospital.</i>

664
01:24:41,868 --> 01:24:44,955
<i>He passed away a while later.</i>

665
01:24:47,416 --> 01:24:52,087
<i>All these years, I've always felt
like a little boy because of him.</i>

666
01:24:53,338 --> 01:24:56,800
<i>He was someone I could always turn to,
someone to solve all my problems.</i>

667
01:24:58,427 --> 01:25:01,763
<i>Packing up his stuff that evening,</i>

668
01:25:02,180 --> 01:25:04,433
<i>I felt like a grown-up
for the first time.</i>

669
01:25:07,936 --> 01:25:09,938
<i>But I don't wanna be a grown-up.</i>

670
01:25:12,065 --> 01:25:14,610
<i>I sure wish Dad
could always be with me!</i>

671
01:25:28,790 --> 01:25:33,211
<i>When I left the hotel,
the videotape was all I took with me.</i>

672
01:25:34,379 --> 01:25:36,590
<i>I watched it over and over
before I left.</i>

673
01:27:22,362 --> 01:27:25,574
<i>Watching Dad cook in the kitchen,
I feel very happy,</i>

674
01:27:26,992 --> 01:27:30,162
<i>Though I know
I'll never taste his steaks again,</i>

675
01:27:31,663 --> 01:27:34,583
<i>I'll never forget how they tasted</i>

676
01:27:40,839 --> 01:27:43,467
<i>You again?
I'll be damned!</i>

677
01:27:43,592 --> 01:27:45,510
<i>Stop pulling my hair!
You promised!</i>

678
01:27:45,677 --> 01:27:48,263
You should know not to touch it.

679
01:27:48,388 --> 01:27:50,515
I'd love to be your customer.

680
01:27:50,682 --> 01:27:52,601
Did I ever say no?

681
01:27:53,059 --> 01:27:54,853
Did I?

682
01:27:55,020 --> 01:27:58,523
Look at me! How do I look?
Don't touch me!

683
01:27:58,690 --> 01:28:00,275
My wife has gone to China.

684
01:28:00,400 --> 01:28:03,820
I have some business to take care of.

685
01:28:03,945 --> 01:28:06,698
Give me three hours.
I promise I'll be back on time.

686
01:28:06,823 --> 01:28:09,284
Three hours, okay?
Three hours.

687
01:28:11,286 --> 01:28:12,829
Two hours?

688
01:28:12,954 --> 01:28:15,707
It's a deal.
Two hours and I'll be back.

689
01:28:16,708 --> 01:28:19,211
Come on, trust me.
We're old friends now, aren't we?

690
01:28:19,377 --> 01:28:22,714
It's a small world. We keep running
into each other. <i>Two</i> hours.

691
01:28:22,839 --> 01:28:24,758
Trust me, please!

692
01:28:24,883 --> 01:28:27,719
You have my word.
We're brothers, right?

693
01:28:31,223 --> 01:28:33,183
<i>You want it written in blood?</i>

694
01:28:34,059 --> 01:28:35,644
<i>You gotta be kidding!</i>

695
01:28:36,728 --> 01:28:37,979
<i>That's my bone!</i>

696
01:28:38,855 --> 01:28:40,106
<i>Just one, okay?</i>

697
01:28:40,357 --> 01:28:44,069
<i>If you cut them all off,
I won't be able to go out in public!</i>

698
01:28:48,114 --> 01:28:50,742
Could I have some change, please?

699
01:28:58,667 --> 01:28:59,584
Thanks.

700
01:29:04,256 --> 01:29:06,007
I'm downstairs already.

701
01:29:06,758 --> 01:29:08,552
Hurry and come down.

702
01:29:08,802 --> 01:29:09,928
Bye-bye.

703
01:29:18,603 --> 01:29:20,939
<i>It must have just been bad luck.</i>

704
01:29:21,356 --> 01:29:25,151
<i>Soon after Dad died,
Sato-san returned to Japan.</i>

705
01:29:26,570 --> 01:29:28,697
<i>Since I didn't have much in savings,</i>

706
01:29:28,822 --> 01:29:30,782
<i>I could only do what I'm best at..</i>

707
01:29:30,907 --> 01:29:32,576
<i>Being my own boss.</i>

708
01:29:33,118 --> 01:29:35,704
<i>But I was very cautious this time.</i>

709
01:29:35,829 --> 01:29:38,498
<i>I tried to pick the stronger shops.</i>

710
01:29:38,623 --> 01:29:41,376
<i>Ones that wouldn't get hurt easily</i>

711
01:29:41,626 --> 01:29:44,629
<i>Like this one.
Its equipment was mostly steel.</i>

712
01:29:44,796 --> 01:29:46,715
<i>It saves a lot of trouble.</i>

713
01:29:47,507 --> 01:29:49,718
<i>At times I'd run into acquaintances.</i>

714
01:29:49,968 --> 01:29:52,637
<i>Some hadn't changed much.</i>

715
01:29:53,597 --> 01:29:55,724
<i>Others I hardly recognized</i>

716
01:29:56,850 --> 01:29:59,269
<i>I was always glad when I saw them,</i>

717
01:29:59,519 --> 01:30:02,606
<i>even though
they might not remember me.</i>

718
01:30:03,815 --> 01:30:06,735
<i>Of course, there were exceptions.</i>

719
01:30:08,069 --> 01:30:10,405
<i>On August 29, 1995,</i>

720
01:30:10,822 --> 01:30:12,949
<i>I ran into my first love again.</i>

721
01:30:13,950 --> 01:30:15,994
<i>But she seemed to have forgotten me.</i>

722
01:30:18,496 --> 01:30:20,874
<i>I guess I'd gotten too handsome.</i>

723
01:30:29,174 --> 01:30:31,676
- How come you're so late?
- I was busy.

724
01:30:31,843 --> 01:30:32,969
What's he doing?

725
01:30:33,428 --> 01:30:34,846
Who knows?

726
01:30:52,364 --> 01:30:55,325
<i>It was cold that evening.</i>

727
01:30:56,326 --> 01:30:59,579
<i>I hadn't expected winter
to come so soon.</i>

728
01:31:05,543 --> 01:31:08,171
<i>I'm less and less used
to this kind of weather.</i>

729
01:31:09,965 --> 01:31:13,093
<i>Winter seems so long this year.</i>

730
01:31:14,386 --> 01:31:16,638
<i>Though I eat a lot every day,</i>

731
01:31:18,390 --> 01:31:19,975
<i>I still feel cold</i>

732
01:31:22,769 --> 01:31:26,064
<i>I've gotten used to life
without a partner.</i>

733
01:31:27,857 --> 01:31:31,319
<i>Though I work with others at times,</i>

734
01:31:31,444 --> 01:31:34,072
<i>I don't usually have fixed partners.</i>

735
01:31:35,865 --> 01:31:37,993
<i>I've grown more cautious.</i>

736
01:31:40,120 --> 01:31:43,081
<i>I won't make their beds anymore,
for example.</i>

737
01:31:43,581 --> 01:31:46,251
<i>I don't inspect their trash,</i>

738
01:31:48,086 --> 01:31:50,255
<i>'cause I believe
even more strongly now</i>

739
01:31:50,380 --> 01:31:53,675
<i>that the best partners
don't get emotionally involved</i>

740
01:32:52,734 --> 01:32:55,862
<i>You rub elbows
with a lot of people everyday,</i>

741
01:32:56,196 --> 01:32:59,991
<i>Some strangers might become
your friends or even confidants.</i>

742
01:33:00,408 --> 01:33:03,661
<i>So I never turn my back
on a chance to rub elbows.</i>

743
01:33:04,621 --> 01:33:06,748
<i>Sometimes I rub till I bleed</i>

744
01:33:07,082 --> 01:33:09,667
<i>No big deal,
as long as I'm happy,</i>

745
01:33:14,923 --> 01:33:18,134
<i>That night,
I ran into that woman again.</i>

746
01:33:18,802 --> 01:33:21,846
<i>I knew very well we'd never be
friends or confidants.</i>

747
01:33:22,013 --> 01:33:25,183
<i>We'd had too many chances
to rub elbows in the past.</i>

748
01:33:25,683 --> 01:33:28,686
<i>We had rubbed elbows
till our clothes tore, but still no sparks.</i>

749
01:33:29,938 --> 01:33:32,190
<i>Maybe it was the weather,</i>

750
01:33:32,482 --> 01:33:35,944
<i>but that evening I felt a spark.</i>

751
01:34:12,230 --> 01:34:15,567
<i>As I was leaving,
I asked if he'd give me a ride home.</i>

752
01:34:18,069 --> 01:34:20,905
<i>I hadn't ridden
on a motorcycle in a long time.</i>

753
01:34:21,406 --> 01:34:24,409
<i>Actually I hadn't been
that close to a man for a while.</i>

754
01:34:26,452 --> 01:34:28,663
<i>The road wasn't that long,</i>

755
01:34:28,997 --> 01:34:30,999
<i>and I knew I'd be getting off soon.</i>

756
01:34:32,333 --> 01:34:35,753
<i>But at that moment
I felt such warmth.</i>

